subject: Re: The 'er' sound
msgSnippet: Page 20 of the Kingsley Read Quikscript Manual has the answer. In short, it is letter #36 + #25.
messageBody:
Page 20 of the Kingsley Read Quikscript Manual has the answer. In
short, it is letter #36 + #25.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "Paul" <euphoniumguy521@...> wrote:
>
> I'm rather new to the whole Read Alphabet/Quikscript so please forgive
> me for asking the following question:
>
> How does one represent the 'er' sound from 'baker' or the 'ear' from
> 'Earth'?
>
> I'm unsure of the British/American/Australian/Canadian/South African
> ratio here, so for clarification, I speak the General American accent
> of English.
>
> Any help would be greatly appreciated.
>
> -Paul
>
